ummary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating server requirements for testing**\\n\\nI'm considering the evidence regarding the need for a server setup when connecting to an external cluster. While it may be helpful, a server isn't strictly necessary for reaching meaningful coverage. Using Docker for Elasticsearch can be heavy due to security configurations. If the user opts for live integration, they’ll need to account for that. I also want to mention that the artifact includes important libraries for testing without external dependencies. Aiming for a complete JSON object summary sounds good!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering agent guidance**\\n\\nI'm thinking about the agent guidance: it suggests avoiding network-dependent searches or index calls unless properly provisioned. It seems we need to provide information about environmental properties or test setups. If there’s no action, I wonder if we can still provide guidance. There’s also a mention of keeping a deterministic setup empty, especially under `no_action`. Summarizing concisely seems best, ensuring the JSON is valid. Exploring the library could be suggested as well.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"action\": \"no_action\",\n  \"summary\": \"The resolved artifact already brings its JSON-P provider, Jackson runtime dependencies, OpenTelemetry API, and Apache HttpClient 5 transport support; meaningful coverage is reachable through client builders, request/response models, JSON serialization/deserialization, and transport construction without adding Maven dependencies or provisioning Elasticsearch.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"End-to-end indexing/search calls require a running Elasticsearch cluster and authentication/TLS handling, but that is not necessary for meaningful library coverage and would make tests heavier and environment-dependent.\",\n    \"The legacy org.elasticsearch.client.RestClient API is not on the normal classpath; generated tests should prefer the 9.x default Rest5-based ElasticsearchClient.of(...) path or pure model/mapper coverage rather than importing org.elasticsearch.client.RestClient.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0f75385da09c8c71016a40d24007488193a3bd53df7bec64a2\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 2666, "output": 699, "cacheRead": 55808, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 59173, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782633013895, "responseId": "resp_0f75385da09c8c71016a40d23680948193a0f927ba942fd23b"}, "toolResults": []}
